With the rate the price of palladium dropping, the price in USD PM has decreased steadily from October 6th to now. With the current pattern, the price will end up being below 2000.00. This pattern has been altered throughout the month, making it possible that the price may be above 2000.00 but below 2400.00. The other prices are highly unpredictable as the price hasn’t gone below 1600.00 in 2022 and hasn’t been higher than 2400.00 in the month of October. Despite the pricing definitely being altered by the war, the pricing seems to be not as affected when it comes to daily changes in the metal.

While the price fluctuates daily, the it seems to be decreasing on the daily by about 50 to 60 USD every day. While this rate is not concrete by any means, it is nevertheless a rather constant number by which it can be used to infer that on October 21st the price will be 1,987 USD. While the war in Ukraine has greatly affected the price palladium, the numbers seemed to tell a somewhat predictable story on the daily exchange of metals.

RATIONALE REPOST: In relative terms, I'm conflicted because the long, medium, and short terms can either show a rise, a decline, or a stabilization in price. It also seems the pandemic jolted the steady rise a bit. And the war in Ukraine may have further complicated matters. Because we're one month out, I'm going to give more weight to the recent trend upward. It may provide better resolution than a wide-view base rate since overall, the price remains stable and doesn't swing hard up and down in units of a thousand.

From 2008 to 2018, the price of palladium had risen on pace of around 25 percent/year. Project forward until 21 October 2022, this would result in a price between $2650 and $2700. The range between $2.4k and $2,8k therefore seems like a good base value for my prediction. Based on historical evidence, there is roughly a 60 percent chance that the price will trade there in October. I wouldn't want to go higher than 60 percent because while price trajectory seems stable overall, influences like the chip shortage and the following slowdown in car manufacturing - both of which are main palladium customers - has pushed the price far from its mean at times. This could easily happen until October, too. So we have to adapt the base value and determine the other values.
